WEBVTT

00:00:12.210 --> 00:00:13.970
The time...

00:00:13.970 --> 00:00:15.830
We're still good.

00:00:15.830 --> 00:00:18.900
Mail won't be here for another 25 minutes.

00:00:42.550 --> 00:00:43.980
They'll be ready

00:00:43.980 --> 00:00:47.350
for your interview after the photoshoot.
[September, 2021]

00:00:47.350 --> 00:00:52.610
Please do not mention the disbandment
until our vocalist brings it up himself.

00:00:52.610 --> 00:00:54.230
Of course.

00:00:56.320 --> 00:00:59.050
Haru. I'll be the one to introduce you.

00:00:59.050 --> 00:01:01.840
No speaking up until then, alright?

00:01:01.840 --> 00:01:03.180
Yes, ma'am.

00:01:04.160 --> 00:01:07.400
[Suffragette City]

00:01:07.400 --> 00:01:10.620
Suffragette City has arrived.

00:01:12.040 --> 00:01:14.120
Morning, folks!

00:01:14.120 --> 00:01:16.360
Good morning.

00:01:28.170 --> 00:01:30.850
They're really here.

00:01:30.850 --> 00:01:33.430
I shall give a short debriefing.

00:01:38.450 --> 00:01:43.060
<i>His face! The way he holds his cup!
Everything about him is just...</i>

00:01:43.060 --> 00:01:45.460
So cool.

00:01:57.500 --> 00:01:59.080
You okay?

00:01:59.820 --> 00:02:01.150
Yes, ma'am.

00:02:01.150 --> 00:02:03.600
Who's this, Yoshida?

00:02:03.600 --> 00:02:05.700
My apprentice. She's an aspiring journalist.

00:02:05.700 --> 00:02:09.310
My name is Haru Aizawa.

00:02:09.310 --> 00:02:11.620
She's apparently a huge fan of the band.

00:02:11.620 --> 00:02:12.930
Really?

00:02:12.930 --> 00:02:17.230
Yes. I've been a fan since your debut.

00:02:18.700 --> 00:02:22.860
Wow. And now you're here to see us in person?

00:02:22.860 --> 00:02:26.030
Yes. It was quite the journey.

00:02:26.030 --> 00:02:27.760
This won't do.

00:02:28.700 --> 00:02:30.500
What's up, Ouji?

00:03:12.070 --> 00:03:15.410
This girl's head over heels for me.

00:04:21.110 --> 00:04:25.220
[Episode 1]

00:04:29.070 --> 00:04:33.620
[April, 2025]

00:04:36.520 --> 00:04:39.120
Thanks for doing my laundry.

00:04:40.210 --> 00:04:42.800
Ouji! Clothes!

00:04:42.800 --> 00:04:44.950
They're going on right now.

00:04:54.090 --> 00:04:58.110
Hamburger steaks, huh? My favorite.

00:04:59.730 --> 00:05:05.300
Relax with a game.
I'll bring it over when it's done.

00:05:05.300 --> 00:05:07.720
I think I'd rather rest my eyes.

00:05:07.720 --> 00:05:09.820
They're asking for this demo too early.

00:05:09.820 --> 00:05:12.920
I should've gotten another week.

00:05:13.570 --> 00:05:15.980
Don't overwork yourself.

00:05:17.350 --> 00:05:19.740
I only see one share. You're not eating with?

00:05:19.740 --> 00:05:23.140
I have dinner plans today.

00:05:23.140 --> 00:05:25.310
I'll leave once I finish prepping your meals.

00:05:25.310 --> 00:05:28.350
I restocked on milk as well.

00:05:28.350 --> 00:05:30.520
Thanks. Tell me when you leave, yeah?

00:05:30.520 --> 00:05:31.960
Will do.

00:05:38.010 --> 00:05:44.380
His work-tussled look is deadly!

00:05:55.250 --> 00:05:57.320
Ouji?

00:05:57.320 --> 00:05:59.620
I'll be heading out now.

00:06:04.910 --> 00:06:07.220
He must have fallen asleep.

00:06:12.550 --> 00:06:13.610
[Ram3]

00:06:13.610 --> 00:06:16.900
Let me get this straight.

00:06:16.900 --> 00:06:20.010
You're basically his maid?

00:06:20.010 --> 00:06:22.190
She sounds more like his mother to me.

00:06:22.190 --> 00:06:24.500
Aw, you two flatter me!

00:06:24.500 --> 00:06:25.720
Those weren't compliments.

00:06:25.720 --> 00:06:27.760
They were anything but.

00:06:27.760 --> 00:06:31.530
<i>This is Fuyumi,
a working mother I met on the job,</i>

00:06:31.530 --> 00:06:34.730
<i>and Akina, a bachelorette
who's one year my junior.</i>

00:06:34.730 --> 00:06:37.260
<i>We often meet to chat over a drink or two.</i>

00:06:37.260 --> 00:06:40.160
Your drink, ma'am.

00:06:40.970 --> 00:06:44.280
So what, is he just a gigolo now?

00:06:44.280 --> 00:06:47.010
No, he does producer work.

00:06:47.010 --> 00:06:48.870
Just this morning, he was busy composing.

00:06:48.870 --> 00:06:51.290
I get it. Musicians are an addictive species.

00:06:51.290 --> 00:06:52.830
You do, Fuyumi?

00:06:52.830 --> 00:06:55.810
I thought your husband
was a licensed architect.

00:06:55.810 --> 00:06:59.220
How nice of him to always let you join us.

00:06:59.220 --> 00:07:03.950
Before we married though,
I was into standoffish musicians I styled,

00:07:03.950 --> 00:07:08.010
who were actually sweethearts deep down.

00:07:08.010 --> 00:07:10.890
Yes, that sort of gap is to die for.

00:07:10.890 --> 00:07:15.200
I get the charm of a gap,
but how are musicians "addictive"?

00:07:15.200 --> 00:07:17.970
You don't even have sex with this guy.

00:07:17.970 --> 00:07:20.260
- S...
- What's the point of staying with him?

00:07:23.140 --> 00:07:26.150
The point, you say...

00:07:26.150 --> 00:07:28.170
You and your foreign standards.

00:07:28.170 --> 00:07:30.400
I'm asking an honest question here.

00:07:30.400 --> 00:07:34.070
How popular was this "Ouji" dude anyway?

00:07:34.070 --> 00:07:37.180
Kazuhiro Ouji, former bassist of the band,
"Suffragette City".

00:07:37.180 --> 00:07:41.010
<i>Performed once at Budokan,
twice for a drama, and once for a commercial.</i>

00:07:41.010 --> 00:07:44.870
<i>They seduce with their melodies,
and mesmerize with their harmonies.</i>

00:07:44.870 --> 00:07:50.050
<i>Their vocalist, Suzuki's enchanting voice,
made them especially popular.</i>

00:07:50.050 --> 00:07:52.430
Leave it to a fangirl to be knowledgeable.

00:07:52.430 --> 00:07:58.190
Though all members had a following,
Ouji was by far the most popular, right?

00:07:58.190 --> 00:08:02.870
That's right! He was often in photoshoots
with famous actresses, too!

00:08:02.870 --> 00:08:04.810
Why do you look so happy about that?

00:08:04.810 --> 00:08:08.840
Seeing him on stage costs extra, after all.

00:08:08.840 --> 00:08:12.970
The one other thing I'll say about musicians?

00:08:12.970 --> 00:08:14.170
They've got sexy fingers.

00:08:14.170 --> 00:08:15.460
Totally!

00:08:15.460 --> 00:08:17.630
Hitting those bass strings.

00:08:17.630 --> 00:08:19.460
Spreading fingers wide on a keyboard.

00:08:19.460 --> 00:08:22.850
And don't forget, stroking a microphone.

00:08:22.850 --> 00:08:24.830
I'm starting to see your point.

00:08:24.830 --> 00:08:28.290
Then his stage presence charmed you good?

00:08:28.290 --> 00:08:33.050
Oh, no. I knew nothing about music
before encountering Suffragettes.

00:08:33.050 --> 00:08:35.620
- Huh?
- I had no hobbies,

00:08:35.620 --> 00:08:40.070
and went straight to employment
after college.

00:08:40.070 --> 00:08:43.110
<i>I had no qualms with my life, until...</i>

00:08:46.610 --> 00:08:49.160
[MUSIC GUIDE]

00:08:51.990 --> 00:08:56.310
<i>I met him, during one fateful lunch break.</i>

00:08:56.310 --> 00:09:00.040
<i>Despite the small article,
I was instantly hooked.</i>

00:09:00.870 --> 00:09:05.970
<i>I knew then,
that I'd fallen hard for this man.</i>

00:09:10.160 --> 00:09:12.730
I desperately felt the need to see him.

00:09:13.610 --> 00:09:17.730
I think you were practically his stalk...

00:09:17.730 --> 00:09:21.410
Every interview I read
only made me fall harder for him.

00:09:21.410 --> 00:09:23.680
I wanted to be the one hearing his stories.

00:09:23.680 --> 00:09:26.200
So I quit my stable job,
took a writing course,

00:09:26.200 --> 00:09:28.760
begged my mentor to let me accompany her,

00:09:28.760 --> 00:09:30.820
and participated
in their disbandment interview.

00:09:30.820 --> 00:09:31.950
Isn't that fate?

00:09:31.950 --> 00:09:34.030
More like an obsession.

00:09:34.030 --> 00:09:38.360
But you never wanted to actually date him?

00:09:38.360 --> 00:09:39.850
No, I would never.

00:09:39.850 --> 00:09:44.070
Right? One night stands
are way easier to deal with.

00:09:44.070 --> 00:09:45.500
That's more out of the question.

00:09:45.500 --> 00:09:47.980
- Really?
- Of course.

00:09:47.980 --> 00:09:51.060
Besides, he was in a relationship
with Keiko Kotani when we first met.

00:09:51.060 --> 00:09:53.760
What? That parenting influencer?

00:09:53.760 --> 00:09:55.160
She was a model, back in the day.

00:09:55.160 --> 00:10:01.340
Rather than be a lover with a deadline,

00:10:01.340 --> 00:10:04.560
I'd rather be an unassuming bystander.

00:10:04.560 --> 00:10:09.050
A background extra,
that could stay by his side, forever.

00:10:09.050 --> 00:10:11.870
That's how dazzling he was to me.

00:10:26.240 --> 00:10:28.370
<i>The hamburger steak was delicious.</i>
[Ouji]

00:10:43.920 --> 00:10:45.130
I'm home.

00:10:45.130 --> 00:10:47.520
Welcome home!

00:10:47.520 --> 00:10:49.570
I'm home, sweetie.

00:10:49.570 --> 00:10:51.030
You were late.

00:10:51.030 --> 00:10:53.360
Sorry, the girls and I were having fun.

00:10:53.360 --> 00:10:55.020
I'm sleeping with Mommy tonight!

00:10:55.020 --> 00:10:59.380
Are you now?

00:11:09.140 --> 00:11:11.520
Still showering, Akina?

00:11:11.520 --> 00:11:13.840
Can I join you?

00:11:15.000 --> 00:11:16.900
Feel free.

00:11:23.000 --> 00:11:25.180
Akina.

00:11:34.820 --> 00:11:36.500
[Busi-CAFE]

00:11:40.300 --> 00:11:41.630
Morning, Haru.

00:11:41.630 --> 00:11:43.710
Shibuya! You're here today?

00:11:43.710 --> 00:11:47.840
Sure am. The home office
was getting a bit stifling.

00:11:47.840 --> 00:11:49.270
Likewise.

00:11:49.270 --> 00:11:51.300
My condolences.

00:11:51.300 --> 00:11:53.690
Forced to write more clickbait?

00:11:53.690 --> 00:11:57.530
Yeah. Something that'll "do numbers".

00:11:57.530 --> 00:12:00.210
Why can't they leave that stuff to AI?

00:12:00.210 --> 00:12:03.310
I remember your great writing
from when we worked together.

00:12:03.310 --> 00:12:07.810
Reminiscing about the past,
at your young age?

00:12:07.810 --> 00:12:10.220
Hey, what's that supposed to mean?

00:12:11.900 --> 00:12:13.530
[Incoming Call: Ouji]

00:12:15.180 --> 00:12:17.000
Be right back.

00:12:18.160 --> 00:12:19.550
Hello? Ouji?

00:12:19.550 --> 00:12:20.980
<i>I...</i>

00:12:22.400 --> 00:12:25.140
I think I'm seriously ill.

00:12:25.910 --> 00:12:27.730
This might be bad.

00:12:27.730 --> 00:12:30.550
<i>Oh my gosh, he sounds so pitiful.</i>

00:12:32.190 --> 00:12:34.830
Are you alright?

00:12:34.830 --> 00:12:36.840
Of course not. Why else would I be calling?

00:12:36.840 --> 00:12:38.890
What?

00:12:38.890 --> 00:12:42.230
You're making my head hurt.

00:12:42.230 --> 00:12:44.230
So...

00:12:44.230 --> 00:12:46.240
Sorry.

00:12:46.240 --> 00:12:50.940
Could you grab me something
with electrolytes from the store?

00:12:50.940 --> 00:12:54.070
Of course. I'll be right there.

00:12:57.150 --> 00:12:59.320
See you around, Shibuya.

00:13:00.200 --> 00:13:01.690
[Hiromaru Convenience Store]

00:13:01.690 --> 00:13:03.730
<i>Don't forget Vitamin B1, and Zinc, too!</i>
[Fuyumi]

00:13:03.730 --> 00:13:05.950
<i>An emergency spare key? You are his mom.</i>
[Akina]

00:13:05.950 --> 00:13:07.250
<i>Haru, what about your deadline?</i>

00:13:07.250 --> 00:13:10.100
<i>Seeing Ouji will motivate me 1000%!</i>
[Haru]

00:13:15.360 --> 00:13:16.640
Taxi!

00:13:16.640 --> 00:13:18.790
Don't turn, darn it.

00:13:47.260 --> 00:13:49.760
Ouji!

00:13:53.880 --> 00:13:56.070
I'm coming in.

00:14:07.830 --> 00:14:11.050
Ouji, are you okay?

00:14:12.990 --> 00:14:14.640
Ouji?

00:14:17.090 --> 00:14:20.160
Ouji? Ouji!

00:14:20.160 --> 00:14:22.600
Ouji! Ouji!

00:14:22.600 --> 00:14:26.220
Ouji. Ouji!

00:14:26.220 --> 00:14:28.190
Ouji!

00:14:47.960 --> 00:14:49.900
What the...

00:14:49.900 --> 00:14:52.660
Don't "what the" me.

00:14:52.660 --> 00:14:55.940
Here, tissues.

00:15:01.560 --> 00:15:03.950
You were this close to suffering pneumonia.

00:15:03.950 --> 00:15:07.960
And why would you drink wine when you're ill?

00:15:07.960 --> 00:15:09.820
I thought it'd help me to sleep.

00:15:09.820 --> 00:15:13.160
Take your medicine instead.
You're nearing 40, you know?

00:15:13.160 --> 00:15:15.580
Don't think you can
match your rowdy twenties.

00:15:15.580 --> 00:15:17.100
I get that.

00:15:17.100 --> 00:15:19.230
No, you don't.

00:15:19.230 --> 00:15:26.420
Please eat, and sleep properly!
What if you collapsed, with no one to help?

00:15:27.730 --> 00:15:29.860
That's it.

00:15:29.860 --> 00:15:31.220
Huh?

00:15:33.210 --> 00:15:37.340
I'll move in.

00:15:38.620 --> 00:15:40.000
What? Why?

00:15:40.000 --> 00:15:42.200
You have a room you're using for storage.

00:15:42.200 --> 00:15:43.460
That's plenty for me.

00:15:43.460 --> 00:15:44.900
I'll pay 50,000 yen for rent.

00:15:44.900 --> 00:15:49.280
Since your room is on the second floor,

00:15:49.280 --> 00:15:50.950
you can still bring girls in, no problem.

00:15:50.950 --> 00:15:52.930
What are you talking about?

00:15:52.930 --> 00:15:54.820
I'll never enter your private quarters.

00:15:54.820 --> 00:15:58.090
Just let me check up on you every three days.

00:15:58.090 --> 00:16:00.580
So you want to cohabit with me?

00:16:00.580 --> 00:16:02.950
N-No!

00:16:02.950 --> 00:16:07.520
We'd be roommates.
Our privacies are entirely intact.

00:16:07.520 --> 00:16:09.890
I only wish to make sure you're healthy.

00:16:09.890 --> 00:16:11.310
You're that worried about me?

00:16:11.310 --> 00:16:13.380
Of course I am.

00:16:13.380 --> 00:16:17.290
You already collapsed last year
after WagaTsuma Fest.

00:16:17.290 --> 00:16:22.100
Because of the... stone.

00:16:22.100 --> 00:16:26.160
Oh, right. My kidney stone.

00:16:26.160 --> 00:16:28.480
Don't make me recall something so mortifying.

00:16:28.480 --> 00:16:31.120
It was more than just mortifying.

00:16:31.120 --> 00:16:32.360
That's nothing to forget about.

00:16:32.360 --> 00:16:34.220
Yeah, now I remember.

00:16:34.220 --> 00:16:35.900
That stone hurt like hell.

00:16:35.900 --> 00:16:40.860
I was there for a job, and ended up
accompanying you to the hospital.

00:16:40.860 --> 00:16:43.280
That's when you gave me a spare key.

00:16:43.280 --> 00:16:45.820
Didn't I show you the stone that popped out?

00:16:45.820 --> 00:16:47.330
You certainly did.

00:16:47.330 --> 00:16:50.380
You cried your eyes out
while clutching that thing.

00:16:50.380 --> 00:16:53.770
- Hilarious.
- It was not funny.

00:16:53.770 --> 00:16:58.820
I was so relieved to see you
no longer in pain.

00:16:58.820 --> 00:17:00.930
Sorry.

00:17:00.930 --> 00:17:03.050
Jeez...

00:17:12.970 --> 00:17:18.040
You know, there's one thing about you I like.

00:17:19.210 --> 00:17:21.100
W-What?

00:17:22.010 --> 00:17:23.570
Something you like?

00:17:23.570 --> 00:17:29.190
Despite always visiting,
you never step foot into my room.

00:17:29.190 --> 00:17:36.600
Of course I don't.
Your room is your creative sanctuary.

00:17:36.600 --> 00:17:37.960
Creative sanctuary, huh?

00:17:37.960 --> 00:17:43.520
You said you'd touch your bass every night
in an interview from 2018.

00:17:43.520 --> 00:17:47.010
I touch other things in there, too.

00:17:47.010 --> 00:17:49.220
Wha... Jeez...

00:17:51.660 --> 00:17:56.190
You must've been raised in a good family.

00:18:00.660 --> 00:18:02.420
How old are you again?

00:18:02.420 --> 00:18:06.180
Me? I'm currently 29.

00:18:06.180 --> 00:18:09.970
I turn 30 next month.

00:18:10.970 --> 00:18:14.980
A 30 and 37-year-old living together.

00:18:14.980 --> 00:18:16.830
Sounds odd, don't you think?

00:18:19.420 --> 00:18:21.180
So, how about this?

00:18:28.780 --> 00:18:30.840
Let's just get married.

00:18:34.850 --> 00:18:37.020
WHAT?

00:18:37.900 --> 00:18:40.990
[Welcome to Kazuhiro and Haru's Wedding]

00:18:42.380 --> 00:18:46.580
How is this being a "background extra"?

00:18:46.580 --> 00:18:48.380
They're moving fast.

00:18:48.380 --> 00:18:50.310
They could learn to take it slow.

00:18:50.310 --> 00:18:52.100
Truly.

00:18:52.100 --> 00:18:56.100
Even so, I'm happy for her.

00:18:56.100 --> 00:18:58.060
Me too.

00:18:58.060 --> 00:19:01.370
I never thought they'd marry.

00:19:01.370 --> 00:19:03.840
Neither did I.

00:19:03.840 --> 00:19:06.650
I'm practically their cupid.

00:19:21.180 --> 00:19:24.030
- Can I come in?
- Sure.

00:19:27.040 --> 00:19:30.020
Why does the bride look so stiff?

00:19:30.020 --> 00:19:33.700
Because none of this feels real.

00:19:33.700 --> 00:19:38.840
I mean, you and I are getting married.

00:19:38.840 --> 00:19:40.410
Why?

00:19:40.410 --> 00:19:43.250
- Don't want to?
- No, far from it.

00:19:43.250 --> 00:19:46.350
But we're even holding a ceremony.

00:19:46.350 --> 00:19:49.670
Our invitations already had people shocked.

00:19:49.670 --> 00:19:51.930
A ceremony would leave them stunned.

00:19:51.930 --> 00:19:54.200
This is a once-in-a-lifetime event for you,

00:19:54.200 --> 00:19:56.160
and you're using it to shock people?

00:19:56.160 --> 00:19:59.150
Reasons for marriage
are a dime a dozen, right?

00:19:59.150 --> 00:20:00.780
- Not that I'd know.
- Ouji...

00:20:00.780 --> 00:20:02.120
And what about you?

00:20:02.120 --> 00:20:04.770
Your serious-looking parents

00:20:04.770 --> 00:20:06.150
gave me their blessings in an instant.

00:20:06.150 --> 00:20:08.160
They certainly did.

00:20:08.160 --> 00:20:12.560
I mean, the protagonist proposed
to an extra. How could they say no?

00:20:12.560 --> 00:20:16.680
- Pardon?
- And now I've become the heroine.

00:20:16.680 --> 00:20:19.990
Am I really fit for this role?

00:20:19.990 --> 00:20:23.640
What should we do, Ouji?

00:20:27.130 --> 00:20:30.200
We'll need to figure out names.

00:20:30.200 --> 00:20:33.800
- Huh?
- I mean, now you're an "Ouji", too.

00:20:40.520 --> 00:20:41.970
Haru?

00:20:43.070 --> 00:20:46.380
<i>I can hear the sweet wedding bells.</i>

00:20:49.800 --> 00:20:54.550
<i>This background extra
is finally getting her moment to shine!</i>

00:20:59.060 --> 00:21:00.440
I'll have to get going.

00:21:00.440 --> 00:21:04.370
Right. See you soon, Kazu...

00:21:04.370 --> 00:21:09.000
One more thing.
We're good with not getting physical, right?

00:21:11.830 --> 00:21:16.730
Phy... Physical...

00:21:16.730 --> 00:21:18.980
Like, our bodies?

00:21:18.980 --> 00:21:20.450
In the literal sense?

00:21:20.450 --> 00:21:22.720
Yeah. It's all off the table.

00:21:22.720 --> 00:21:25.440
Our relationship's not like that, you know?

